categorical plot¶

  • Categorical scatterplots:
    • stripplot() (with kind="strip"; the default)
    • swarmplot() (with kind="swarm")
  • Categorical distribution plots:
    • boxplot() (with kind="box")
    • violinplot() (with kind="violin")
    • boxenplot() (with kind="boxen")
  • Categorical estimate plots:
    • pointplot() (with kind="point")
    • barplot() (with kind="bar")
    • countplot() (with kind="count")
In [106]:
sns.catplot("day",'tip',data=tips) # default kind is strip
Out[106]:
<seaborn.axisgrid.FacetGrid at 0x1f7e27b42c8>

In [132]:
num_col = tips.columns[tips.dtypes!='category']
In [133]:
val = 1
for i in range(len(num_col)):
    for j in range(len(num_col)):
        plt.subplot(3,3,val)
        plt.scatter(tips[num_col[i]],tips[num_col[j]])
        plt.title(num_col[i]+'_'+num_col[j])
        val += 1
